condemning images, as M. Calfhill doth the 2.
of Nice, allowing them. The best way then as Augustine
conncelleth ye heretike Maximinus, were to giue
ouer the hold of Councels on both sides, &amp; try ye matter
by the word of God.
               It is a fond quarrel yt he picketh to M. Calfhill, of ye
time when ye Eliberine councel was kept, if it be auncienter
then hee supposeth, it is of greater credite, for ye
latter times were more corrupt. And whereas he gi
