miracles were done by imposition of handes, yet it
followeth not therefore, that euery Church must haue
imposition of handes. Againe, not onely Cankers,
but also Fistulaes, tooth ache, and many other diseases
haue bene healed by charmes. And yet these
charmes are not iustifiable thereby, much lesse to be
brought into the Church, as wholesome ceremonies
and prayers.
