coniuration in which be so many names of God, and
good words, to be an holy peece of worke. Therfore it
is not many good parts abused to make a wicked thing
good, that can iustifie the Masse, which is an hurrible
blasphemie against the death and onely sacrifice of
Christ. But M. Calfhil doth not satisfie him, where he
citing out of Albertus Magnus, That Christ did blesse the
sacrament with a certeine signe of his hand, as Iacob laide his
