done to the Princes seate, and to the Prince him selfe.
And wheras Arnobius saith expresly, &amp; absolutely we
worship no crosses, he expoundeth it, we worship them
not as Gods. Such expositions may auoyde all authorities.
The Gentiles which knewe the Christians worshipped

but one God, did not obiuct worshipping of
crosses vnto them as Gods.
