is proued by many arguments to be none of
Hieronymes writing, but of one of much later time.
               
                  
Thus hath Martial against the true testimonies of
the fathers, nothing to oppose, but their counterfetted
authorities, and false inscribed writings. Concerning
Hieronymes adoration of the mangar and incunabula
the cradle of Christ, which Martial so often called the
