no such adoration, as the Papistes giue vnto their
images, but a reuerent estimatiō, as of an ancient, holy
monumēt, wherin yet I wil not altogether excuse Hierome
of superstitious affectiō, as I wil not charge him
wt idolatrie. For Chrysostomes iudgment of worshipping
ye crosse, I refer the reader as before, to Cap. 13. or
12. of mine answere to D. Sand. booke of images. To
